programme.title: The Young and the Restless
programme.desc: An iconic, enduring soap opera, this is the steamer set in Genoa City, where the Newman and Abbott dynasties stir it up in the bedroom and the boardroom. Best known for long-term love triangles, issue-oriented plots, a multi-ethnic cast and slick production values, 'Y&R' has been showered with Emmys, launched countless careers and spawned the equally lavish 'The Bold and the Beautiful.' Former cast members include Tom Selleck and David Hasselhoff. (New).

programme.title: The Bold and the Beautiful
programme.desc: The high-glam soap about L.A.'s fashionable and fertile Forrester clan was designed as a sister soap to the popular 'The Young and the Restless,' and quickly won ratings and global fans with cast crossovers, exotic remotes, glossy runway shows and fast-paced storylines about beautiful people behaving badly. In 2004, the show introduced a new family, the Marones, and recruited several nighttime alums to beef up the cast. And to create a little chaos. (New).

programme.title: American Experience
programme.desc: "Zoot Suit Riots" recalls a week of violence that rocked L.A. in June 1943, pitting Mexican-Americans against Anglos. The hour uses atmospheric re-creations and interviews with historians and people who lived through it to chart a year of steadily rising tension. One key event: an August 1942 altercation in which a Mexican-American man died. The defendants were also Mexican-American, but the trial inflamed prejudices and on June 3, 1943, says narrator Hector Elizondo, "the city exploded." (Repeat).

programme.title: Von Ryan's Express
programme.desc: During WWII, a number of captured British soldiers are led by an American in an attempt to escape an Italian POW camp by stealing a train and riding it to Switzerland. (Repeat).

programme.title: None But the Brave
programme.desc: Frank Sinatra took over the director's chair for the first (and only) time in this WWII drama, about Japanese and American soldiers stranded on a remote Pacific island. They agree to a truce to focus on bringing help to the island, but once either side's forces reach them, the fighting will pick up where it left off. (Repeat).

programme.title: Twelve O'Clock High
programme.desc: Best Picture nominee about an embattled Army Air Corps general who takes over the 918th Bomber Group for raids over World War II Germany when he deems their previous commander has gotten too close with his men. (Repeat).

programme.title: Rio Conchos
programme.desc: An ex-Confederate Army Officer leads a scouting unit of four on a secret mission to investigate the selling of stolen weapons to Apaches. Based on the novel by Clair Huffaker. (Repeat).

programme.title: The Comancheros
programme.desc: A Texas Ranger runs across a gang of white renegades, called the Comancheros, who are trading guns and other contraband with marauding Comanches from a secret hideout in Mexico. He goes undercover as a partner with a vicious outlaw who is a contact man with the Comancheros and knows the whereabouts of their hideout in Mexico. Director Michael Curtiz's last film. (Repeat).

programme.title: The Undefeated
programme.desc: Feuding Union and Confederate Generals who battled each other during the Civil War clash again as they each lead a different group of people out west, but eventually work together when attacked by Mexicans. (Repeat).

programme.title: Point Blank
programme.desc: A cuckolded husband will stop at nothing in his quest for revenge as he takes on the Los Angeles mob after his wife and her gangster boyfriend try to kill him and make off with the loot from a heist they pulled. An adaptation of Donald E. Westlake's crime opus "The Hunter." (Repeat).

programme.title: Jeremiah Johnson
programme.desc: A Rocky Mountain trapper assimilates with Native Americans in the 1820s, but becomes a legendary Indian killer after the Crow tribe kills his family in retaliation for leading the U.S. cavalry on a rescue mission through a sacred burial site. (Repeat).

programme.title: Stagecoach
programme.desc: A diverse ensemble of travelers must work together to defend their stagecoach against Geronimo and Apache attacks. Color remake of John Ford's 1939 western classic. (Repeat).

programme.title: Stagecoach
programme.desc: A group of people traveling through Indian country on a stagecoach are pressured by the threat posed by Geronimo and discover which among them can stay cool in a crisis. (Repeat).

programme.title: The Silencers
programme.desc: A boozing, womanizing spy is coaxed out of retirement by an ex-girlfriend. His mission is to stop the evil Big O organization, whose leader plots to sabotage an atomic missile and thus spark World War III. (Repeat).

programme.title: Murderers' Row
programme.desc: A sleuth (Dean Martin) copes with beautiful girls and an archvillain (Karl Malden). Suzie: Ann-Margret. Dr. Solaris: Richard Eastham. Coco: Camilla Sparv. Ironhead: Tom Reese. MacDonald: James Gregory. Henry Levin directed. (Repeat).

programme.title: The Bounty Killer
programme.desc: Easterner (Dan Duryea) kills an outlaw, becomes a professional gun-for-hire, and hastens to ruin. Richard Arlen, Buster Crabbe, Fuzzy Knight, Johnny Mack Brown, Bob Steele, Audrey Dalton. Good story, belabored in the telling. Directed by Spencer Gordon Bennet. (Repeat).

programme.title: Big Bad Mama
programme.desc: Farcical melodrama with Angie Dickinson as a bank robber of the 1930s. Baxter: William Shatner. Fred: Tom Skerritt. Billy Jean: Susan Sennett. Polly: Robbie Lee. Barney: Noble Willingham. Directed by Steve Carver. (Repeat).

programme.title: Crazy Mama
programme.desc: Melodrama covering 30 years in the criminal lives of an Arkansas family. Cloris Leachman, Stuart Whitman. Sheba: Ann Sothern. Albertson: Jim Backus. Shawn: Donny Most. Cheryl: Linda Purl. Snake: Bryan Englund. Sheba (1932): Tisha Sterling. Bertha: Merie Earle. Ella Mae: Sally Kirkland. Daniel: Clint Kimbrough. Homer: Vince Barnett. Directed by Jonathan Demme. (Repeat).

programme.title: North to Alaska
programme.desc: Prospecting partners in Alaska find gold, prompting one to ask the other if he will escort the man's fiance on a journey to join them. (Repeat).

programme.title: Escape From Fort Bravo
programme.desc: In the Arizona territory, a ruthless Union Army captain undertakes a mission to recapture escaped Confederate prisoners and runs into an Apache hunting party. (Repeat).

programme.title: Little Women
programme.desc: Adaptation of Louisa May Alcott's classic slice of Americana about the four spirited March sisters and details their adventures, ambitions and romances in 1860s Massachusetts. (Repeat).

programme.title: Cactus Flower
programme.desc: A middle-aged dentist has taken on a much younger girlfriend. At first feigning fear of commitment because of his wife and children, and then falling for his young lover, the dentist implores the help of his nurse to pose as the wife he claims to have. (Repeat).

programme.title: Hopscotch
programme.desc: A CIA operative retires when his boss finds out that he let a KGB assassin escape. The operative begins writing a tell-all memoir, which causes him to go on the run from his former employers when they find out. (Repeat).

programme.title: The Men Who Stare at Goats
programme.desc: This uproarious comedy stars Ewan McGregor as a reporter who helps a U.S. soldier find the officer responsible for creating a top-secret program that trains warriors to develop psychic powers. The two learn that the officer is engaged in a personal feud with a spiritualist, and the program itself may soon disappear. (Repeat).

programme.title: The Ambushers
programme.desc: Superagent Matt Helm trails another power-mad spy chief, this time in Mexico. His mission is to secure a flying-saucer weapon that's fatal to men, but not to women. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Wrecking Crew
programme.desc: Fourth and final in the Matt Helm series with Dean Martin as the special agent, this time up against some lethal lovelies and a super-villain bent on stealing a billion dollars in gold bullion, which could possibly affect a collapse of the world economy. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Bravados
programme.desc: A rancher arrives in a small western town to witness the hanging of the men whom he holds responsible for the murder of his wife. Through the help of a duplicitous executioner, the gang escape and the vengeful rancher sets out to hunt the fugitives down. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Lady Vanishes
programme.desc: Vintage Hitchcock about an elderly English governess who disappears from a train, a fact that doesn't particularly concern other passengers except for a young lady she'd befriended and who's become convinced that somthing is amiss.(n)

programme.title: The Most Dangerous Game
programme.desc: A psychotic hunter arranges a shipwreck that will allow him to track and kill human prey. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Window
programme.desc: A young boy who is prone to lying claims to have witnessed a killing take place in a neighboring New York City apartment, but can't get anyone to believe him---except the murderers. The film is from a story by Cornell Woolrich, who wrote a similarly themed tale that was adapted for Hitchcock's "Rear Window." (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Panic in the Streets

programme.title: Mildred Pierce

programme.title: Framed

programme.title: The House on 92nd Street
programme.desc: Nazi spies in America recruit a German-American college student, who promptly goes to the FBI. The Feds convince him to be come a double agent, and help them find the leader of this clan of saboteurs. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: They Won't Believe Me
